"script": "Cut off this animal's leg, and it just grows a perfect new one. The axolotl is a salamander that never quite grows up, keeping its feathery gills for life. But its real superpower is healing. Lose a limb, and within weeks the bones, muscles, and nerves rebuild themselves, good as new. And it doesn't stop at legs. It can regrow parts of its heart, its spine, even pieces of its own brain, with no scar left behind. Scientists study it obsessively, because if we could copy this trick, we might one day heal the same way.",
